text: Fanni Juhász (born 31 March 1981) is a Hungarian pole vaulter who competes in international level events. Her greatest achievement was winning a bronze medal at the 2000 World Junior Championships in Athletics in Santiago, Chile. ==References== Category:1981 births Category:Living people Category:Sportspeople from Debrecen Category:Hungarian female pole vaulters
